{"word":"τραγῳδέω","slug":"τραγῳδέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τραγῳδέω</b></el> <el>(τρᾰγῳδέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τραγῳδός'><el>τραγῳδός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to act a tragedy</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> objecti, <i>to represent in tragedy</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be the subject of a tragedy</i>, <b><a href='S:Isocrates'>Isocr.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to tell in tragic phrase, to declaim</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}